The paper deals with multi-modal learning, specifically in the context of coreference resolution. The paper discusses the use of high-level features of images and text, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning model, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal data, which could suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
